All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AlternativeDisplay
Defines a variety of possible alternative displays for use with the frontend app.
AlternativeDisplay.AlternativeDisplays
Enum listing off current possible alternative displays To add additional displays, simply add a new value here and modify the behavior of the frontend app accordingly
Field
The Field class holds the data.
Field
The Field class represents the graphical fields present on the form.
FormData
The FormData class holds data that has been filled by users, in its Group and Field classes ; the structure of these groups and classes mirrors the structure of the associated prefab.
FormDataController
Controller for the FormData API Answers requests to the /api/formdata/ route
FormDataRepository
Repository that queries the database to fetch FormData objects in the form_data collection.
FormDataService
Service that acts as an interface between the repository and other classes which may which to fetch data from the database.
FreelyFormsApplication
 
Generator
Generator service to automatically generate basic data that may be then added to the database.
Group
The Group class holds the fields containing data, in a structure mirroring the group of the same name in the Prefab class that links to the holding FormData.
Group
The Group class holds the form fields that will be displayed on the front-end for the user to fill.
MaximumRule
Sets a maximum value for either a number, a date or a string length
MinimumRule
Sets a minimum value for either a number, a date or a string length
Prefab
The Prefab class defines and structures forms to be filled in by end users.
PrefabController
Controller for the Prefab API Answers requests to the /api/prefabs/ route
PrefabRepository
Repository that queries the database to fetch Prefab objects in the Prefab collection.
RegexMatch
checks whether a string matches a given regular expression
Rule
The Rule class holds attributes and methods used to define the function and behavior of a field, such as accepted data type or optionality.
Rule.FieldType
Enumeration representing the possible data types
SelectDataSet
Determines a prefab.group.field combination that is to be used as selector values for this prefab.
TypeRule
The TypeRule class is an abstract class designed to be inherited by classes that will have methods and values that may be used to verify form data value validity.
User
User class that may be used to identify and authenticate users
UserController
Controller for the User API Answers requests to the /api/users/ route
UserRepository
Repository that queries the database to fetch User objects in the users collection.
UserService
Service that acts as an interface between the repository and other classes which may which to fetch data from the database.
